                                                                Development of Veroboard
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

June 3rd - 4th : 

Veroboard had shorting issue thus it was ideal to use wires due to the tight deadline. 

Thus final Final Code : 
    Project Status ~ 10 Seconds 
    
    Used a sequential instructions with delays instead of timer as it was more reliable (no excessive current draws thus safe for components). 
    PWM of shoulder motors going DOWN.
    Limit switches were added to control the shoulders going up (for added safety there was a time duration allocated for the shoulders to go up incase
    limit switch fails)



